<h1>TrackedDataLayers</h1>
<p>High-performance real-time entity rendering with smooth animation, decorations, clustering, and interaction.</p>

<blockquote>
    <p><strong>Phase 2 migration:</strong> tracked data is now configured on <code>SgbMap.TrackedDataLayers</code> using <code>TrackedDataLayer&lt;TItem&gt;</code>. Direct <code>&lt;TrackedDataSource /&gt;</code> usage is no longer supported.</p>
</blockquote>

<h2 id="train_tracking">// train_tracking</h2>
<p>This example simulates 47 trains across the Luxembourg rail network. Each train is a tracked entity whose position, rotation, and feature-state properties update every tick without re-creating the underlying MapLibre source.</p>

<p>Features demonstrated:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Map-level tracked orchestration with <code>SgbMap.TrackedDataLayers</code></li>
    <li>Grouped constructor-complete tracked options: visual, behavior, and callbacks</li>
    <li><code>TrackedDataSymbolOptions</code> for icon, position, rotation, and color selectors</li>
    <li>Optional tracked popups via <code>TrackedDataSymbolOptions.PopupSelector</code> (click and hover triggers)</li>
    <li>Multi-layer decorations with conditional display modes (always, hover, selected)</li>
    <li>Zoom-to-dissolve clustering via <code>TrackedDataClusterOptions</code></li>
    <li>Hover and select interaction through feature-state</li>
    <li>Smooth position interpolation via <code>AnimationOptions</code></li>
    <li>SVG-to-data-URI custom icon registration via the map <code>Images</code> parameter</li>
    <li>Style composition with a railway overlay on a Positron base</li>
    <li>Interactive <a href="components/map-legend">LegendMapControl</a> configured in <code>SgbMap.Controls</code>, with custom swatch templates</li>
</ul>

<ExampleView TComponent="TrainTrackingExample"
             AdditionalSources="@(new[] { typeof(TrainTrackingPresentation), typeof(TrainSampleSimulation) })">
